---
// SlicedLabs · studio · © 2026 SlicedLabs — Manifesto / About
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Manifesto — SlicedLabs" description="Own your slice. A food · media · marketing company building in public.">
  <section class="wrap" style="max-width:48rem; padding-block:clamp(2.5rem,7vw,4rem);">
    <p class="mono" data-reveal>the manifesto</p>
    <h1 class="kinetic" data-reveal style="--i:1; font-size:clamp(2.4rem,8vw,5rem);"><span class="blend-text">Own your slice.</span></h1>
    <hr class="blade" data-reveal style="--i:2; max-width:18rem; margin:1.6rem 0 0;" />

    <p data-reveal style="--i:3; font-size:1.25rem; color:var(--muted); margin-top:1.8rem;">
      SlicedLabs is one company: a <strong style="color:var(--ink);">food · media · marketing</strong> brand
      building a real food empire in public — and proving anyone can own their slice by showing exactly how,
      receipts and all.
    </p>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
      <h2 data-reveal>What "own your slice" means</h2>
      <p data-reveal style="color:var(--muted);">
        A slice is something you control end to end — your stack, your audience, your income, your time, your supply.
        We own the audience instead of renting attention. We become the landlord instead of renting the lot.
        We source local now and grow our own later. The same move, repeated at every layer.
      </p>

      <h2 data-reveal>The depth behind it</h2>
      <p data-reveal style="color:var(--muted);">
        This didn't come from nowhere. It's the distilled discipline of the operators we ran from for years —
        value creation, lean systems, selling without sleaze, buying back your time, compounding ownership.
        We don't just quote the playbooks; we <em>run</em> them, on camera, and let the receipts make the argument.
      </p>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="glass glass-ultra island" data-reveal style="margin:2.4rem 0; font-family:var(--font-display); font-size:clamp(1.4rem,4vw,2rem); font-weight:700; line-height:1.18;">
      Everyone sells the dream.<br /><span class="blend-text">We show the machine.</span>
    </blockquote>

    <p data-reveal style="color:var(--muted);">
      The homestead and the skills center are where this is going — they aren't here yet, and we'll say so every time.
    </p>

    <div data-reveal style="margin-top:3rem; text-align:center;">
      <hr class="blade center" style="max-width:10rem; margin:0 auto 1rem;" />
      <p class="mono">build it in public · show the math</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
